<div class='tab-content'>
    <div class='tab-pane active' id='privilege' role='tabpanel'>
        <div class='p-3'>
            <h2 id='basic-privileges' class='title'>Basic and Full Member Privileges</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Upload new models to the Model Library</b></li>
                <li><b>Contribute to the general CoMSES discussion forums, submit job openings and events to the events calendar</b></li>
            </ul>
            <h2 id='full-member-privileges' class='title'>Full Members Privileges</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><b>Create special interest groups on the <a href='https://forum.comses.net'>CoMSES Net Forums</a>.</b></li>
                <li><b>Receive assistance in preparing complex models for submission to the Computational Model Library.</b> This will be on a per-application basis and dependent on available funds for RA support.</li>
                <li><b>Access and contribute to community datasets.</b> Full members may access datasets contributed for model testing, validation, benchmarking, and educational use. Community members are encouraged to help expand and curate these shared resources.</li>
                <li><b>Join the CoMSES Agentic Modeling Working Group.</b> Open to Full Members, the CoMSES Agentic Modeling Working Group advances community practices for integrating AI coding agents into the computational modeling lifecycle. Members collaborate on methods, training materials, and open resources that help modelers use AI effectively for model design, development, documentation, publication, and reuse, while maintaining scientific rigor, transparency, reproducibility, and independent critical thinking. 
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class='tab-pane' id='responsibility' role='tabpanel'>
        <div class='p-3'>
            <h2 id='basic-responsibilities' class='title'>Responsibilities of all CoMSES Network Members</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Cite and acknowledge whose models, software, data, or other resources contribute to your work.</li>
                <li>Develop and use computational models responsibly, ethically, and in ways that advance science and benefit society.</li>
                <li>Share knowledge and expertise with other members and support their growth as modelers, researchers, educators, and practitioners.</li>
                <li>Contribute to a collaborative, inclusive, and intellectually rigorous community.</li>
                <li>Adhere to our <a href='https://github.com/comses/comses.net/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md'>Code of Conduct</a>:
                <ol>
                    <li>Be respectful of different viewpoints, experiences, and backgrounds</li>
                    <li>Give and receive constructive feedback</li>
                    <li>Focus on what best serves the community and advances our shared mission</li>
                    <li>Treat others with courtesy and professionalism</li>
                </ol>
                </li>
            </ul>
        <p>Full members are encouraged to help steward and strengthen the CoMSES.Net community and its shared knowledge resources by:</p>
        <h2 id='full-member-responsibilities' class='title'>Full Member Responsibilities</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Participating in network self-governance and community decision-making</li>
            <li>Assisting with the evaluation and peer review of computational models, research software, and related scholarly resources submitted for publication or certification</li>
            <li>Contributing models, datasets, publications, educational materials, and documentation that advance open science, research reproducibility, interoperability, and reuse</li>
            <li>Supporting community-building, training, mentoring, and educational activities that foster collaboration and knowledge sharing</li>
            <li>Sharing expertise through working groups, discussions, workshops, and other collaborative activities that benefit the broader community</li>
            <li>Serving as resource stewards who help maintain and improve CoMSES.Net's digital infrastructure, community resources, and governance processes</li>
        </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
